<br>
It's neither 100 percent broken nor 100 percent fixed. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-banner-long-3.gif" height=60 width=468 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=british>British</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/31/01 9:20:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top 10 items I hope Verant addresses in 2002</span><hr size=1> I've never killed a mob with a rain spell, however, I DID kill a mob's pet once.<br>
<br>
What's more, is it hit both the mob and its pet for THREE waves, for a total of SIX hits.<br>
<br>
But, again, this was a pet, so somehow the rules must be different.<br>
<br>
However, after several hours of testing in Velketor's, I am still convinced that rains cannot kill actual mobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
Yes, at the very least, there needs to be a /pet stfu command.<br>
<br>
<br>
And TL confirmation boxes...  One of the two needs to go, either the grouping requirement or the confirmation box.  Probably the grouping requirement - I know I would be a LOT more willing to translocate people in accordance with Verant's vision if I didn't have to group with them and risk getting group bugged.<br>
